This paper deals with facial expression editing using a generative adversarial network, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of an expression controller module, which involves learning an expressive and compact expression code, indicating a possible focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of image retrieval and data augmentation, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
